text: Da Cheng kekou mian is my ultimate lunch favourite. The chilli is so good to pair with chewy noodles! Will always need to check operating days before going though, it‚Äôs not always open.

Food court has a lot of food during office hours, decent for the size and location, has a great variety of printing (as the location states ü§£) company located in the building food is agreeable for the price.

Today went lunch with peers, Niang Dou Fu is good as usual.. never failed me.
My colleagues ate the Muslim Rice, they are pleased with the food especially the chicken.. juicy and tasty.
However, one disappointment is the Economy Rice we packed back for one of our colleague.  The minute she opened the box of rice.. She was like what is that... an insect was lying deadly on the vegetables.  She was like omg.. am I going to eat or throw.

The food at Print Media Sinfoodie is quite limited. Only good one is prawn rib noodles. Haven't try the Duck Shop yet

Environment is so so, and at times is quite hot in the afternoon.

The Cai Fan stall uncle was dishonest. He gave me change in $0.50 coins even though he had cash notes and intentionally short-changed me by $2. It was only when I went back to enquire that he returned the $2, and he did not even apologize.
